         <body view="all">
            <ce:sections>
               <ce:para id="cpara01" view="all">This article has been retracted: please see Elsevier Policy on Article Withdrawal (<ce:inter-ref id="int40" xlink:href="https://www.elsevier.com/locate/withdrawalpolicy" xlink:type="simple">https://www.elsevier.com/locate/withdrawalpolicy</ce:inter-ref>).</ce:para>
               <ce:para id="cpara02" view="all">This article has been retracted at the request of the Editor-in-Chief.</ce:para>
               <ce:para id="cpara03" view="all">This article has been retracted at the request of Editor-in-Chief, based on an anonymous complaint to the journal that there are signs of image manipulation in the paper.</ce:para>
               <ce:para id="cpara04" view="all">The concerns are as follows:<ce:list id="cas25">
                     <ce:list-item id="cl10">
                        <ce:label>1.</ce:label>
                        <ce:para id="cpara05" view="all">The photoluminescence data shown in Figure 4 (b) are identical to figures shown in Ceramics International 44 (2018) 5705–5709 <ce:inter-ref id="int41" xlink:href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ceramint.2017.12.223" xlink:type="simple">https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ceramint.2017.12.223</ce:inter-ref> Figure 3 (c) and in Int. J. Hydrogen Energy 44 (2019) 24690-24697 <ce:inter-ref id="int42" xlink:href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijhydene.2019.07.220" xlink:type="simple">https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijhydene.2019.07.220</ce:inter-ref> Figure 7. However, the papers indicate that these are a different material each time.</ce:para>
                     </ce:list-item>
                     <ce:list-item id="cl20">
                        <ce:label>2.</ce:label>
                        <ce:para id="cpara06" view="all">Figure 2 appears to be manipulated: a portion of Fig 2c is magnified in a portion of 2d. This has been demonstrated through image analysis. However, the caption indicates that the images are for different materials.</ce:para>
                     </ce:list-item>
                     <ce:list-item id="cl30">
                        <ce:label>3.</ce:label>
                        <ce:para id="cpara07" view="all">Figure 4 (a) is duplicated from Int. J. Hydrogen Energy 44 (2019) 24690-24697 (Figure 6), with wavelengths below 350 nm cut off.</ce:para>
                     </ce:list-item>
                     <ce:list-item id="cl40">
                        <ce:label>4.</ce:label>
                        <ce:para id="cpara08" view="all">Spectra shown in Figure 3 and Figure 4 (a) appear to be drawn by hand: the curves go backwards at several points, which is impossible.</ce:para>
                     </ce:list-item>
                  </ce:list>
               </ce:para>
               <ce:para id="cpara09" view="all">The manipulation of images and data in this way is a serious offense to the integrity of the scientific community and casts doubts on all the data, and accordingly also the conclusions based on that data in this publication. Due to the above concerns, the Editor decided to retract the paper.</ce:para>
            </ce:sections>
         </body>
